      <item>
        <title>How it is built</title>
        <description>&lt;ul id=&quot;markdown-toc&quot;&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#quick-start&quot; id=&quot;markdown-toc-quick-start&quot;&gt;Quick start&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#about-jekyll&quot; id=&quot;markdown-toc-about-jekyll&quot;&gt;About jekyll&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#about-ruby-eco-behind-jekyll&quot; id=&quot;markdown-toc-about-ruby-eco-behind-jekyll&quot;&gt;About ruby eco behind jekyll&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;quick-start&quot;&gt;Quick start&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;create github account as well as a repository for your site.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;clone source code and push to your own repository.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;git clone https://github.com/luoyan35714/LessOrMore &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;local&lt;/span&gt;-project-dir
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;cd local&lt;/span&gt;-project-dir   
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;git config remote.origin.url your-reposiytory.git  
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;git push origin master&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Go to your repository settings and allow Github Page to source from the master branch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;about-jekyll&quot;&gt;About jekyll&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Jekyll is written in ruby supported by Github Page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you have ruby installed, the following will get you jekyll.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;gem install jekyll &lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will host your site built based on jekyll template on local machine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;jekyll serve &lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you want to specify other host.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;option] --host &lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;about-ruby-eco-behind-jekyll&quot;&gt;About ruby eco behind jekyll&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;nice way to &lt;a href=&quot;http://rvm.io&quot;&gt;install ruby&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://rubygems.org/&quot;&gt;gem&lt;/a&gt; is a ruby library manager. It helps to install ruby packages such as jekyll and bundler.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://bundler.io/&quot;&gt;bundler&lt;/a&gt; is a ruby project dependencies manager. It initialize a ruby project wit a Gemfile, where you list all the dependencies you want to use as well as their versions. So anyone with the same Gemfile can create the same dev environment via one command:&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;bundler install &lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Please reference the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/luoyan35714/LessOrMore&quot;&gt;author&lt;/a&gt; of this jekyll template for more specific instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
